docs.text:
Shehan Caldera


Welcome


Hello World! I'm Shehan (goes by the online handle 
@shehancaldera
). I'm a research student from Edith Cowan University, Western Australia. And I'm currently involved in deep learning for robotics. I like working with machine learning, deep learning, deep reinforcement learning and other robotics projects.


Apart from working with robotics, I like travelling, photography, camping and driving around in my Ford.


If you have any project that you would like my insight or collaboration feel free to email at 
shehancaldera@gmail.com
 with a clear subject line.


Projects I've worked:






Robotic grasping with deep learning






Detecting robotic grasps usign deep convolutional neural networks






Design and development of a tennis ball launching machine






Development of a RGB color detection system






Design of a robotic platform for variable terrains






Grid solving robot for industrial payload delivery 






Find me


Github & LinkedIn : 
@shehancaldera
